From: Daniel Micay <danielmicay@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 17 Sep 2019 18:00:54 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 051/106] mm: slab: trigger BUG if requested object is not a
 slab page

Signed-off-by: Daniel Micay <danielmicay@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Levente Polyak <levente@leventepolyak.net>
Signed-off-by: Thibaut Sautereau <thibaut.sautereau@ssi.gouv.fr>
---
 mm/slab.h | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/mm/slab.h b/mm/slab.h
index 6cc323f1313a..6e4c9c1709a0 100644
--- a/mm/slab.h
+++ b/mm/slab.h
@@ -417,9 +417,13 @@ static inline struct kmem_cache *virt_to_cache(const void *obj)
 	struct page *page;
 
 	page = virt_to_head_page(obj);
+#ifdef CONFIG_BUG_ON_DATA_CORRUPTION
+	BUG_ON(!PageSlab(page));
+#else
 	if (WARN_ONCE(!PageSlab(page), "%s: Object is not a Slab page!\n",
 					__func__))
 		return NULL;
+#endif
 	return page->slab_cache;
 }
 
